Pat Benoy wrote:
> 
> Is it ok to use a 9.6 volt 700 mAh RadioShack batttery instead of the
> 500 mAh battery specifed in the instructions??

I'm sure that would be fine.  The important things seem to be the 9.6
volts and the relatively high current capacity that nicads provide.  The
larger the amp-hour rating, the longer you can go before recharging.

